text: Jack Denning (17 April 1875 – 7 January 1949) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with Collingwood in the Victorian Football League (VFL). He later played with Brunswick in the Victorian Football Association (VFA). == Notes == == External links == * *Jack Denning's profile at Collingwood Forever Category:1875 births Category:1949 deaths Category:Australian rules footballers from Western Australia Category:Collingwood Football Club players Category:Brunswick Football Club players Category:Perth Football Club players
